<Author>Rumples
<Content>Great Location My husband and I stayed at the Regencia Colon Hotel for five nights in December 2008. The location in Barri Gotic close to the cathedral can't be beat for easy access to La Rambla, Palau de la Musica Catalana, Placa de Catalunya, excellent places to eat at many prices, the hop on/hop off bus, and much, much more.Our fifth-floor room was good sized, immaculate and had a comfortable bed and two comfortable padded chairs. Plenty of space existed for hanging and storing items. Amenities included a safe, a flat-screen TV with English channels, a hairdryer and toiletries. The room had two windows with tiny balconies that were decorative rather than useful.If noise bothers you, however, avoid this hotel or bring excellent earplugs.. Street noise that comes in includes vehicular traffic, voices of people in the cathedral area, and an amazing clatter at 1 a.m. that appears to be a trash collection service in action. Walls are paper thin so you can hear conversations, hairdryers in use and clanging showers.The hotel offers a good buffet breakfast with both hot and cold items for 11.77 euros, including tax. There are many less expensive alternatives in the neighborhood for those who don't require a lot of food in the morning. We did not consider the room rate to be good value during the Christmas period when we stayed at the hotel. Unlike other reviewers, we found the room to be high priced. That's because of the holiday rate increase when Barcelona becomes a major destination.Though the desk staff proved to be friendly and helpful, one man really pushed taking the taxi to the airport, claiming that it would be a fixed price if booked through the hotel. The price proved to be higher than what was quoted at the hotel and we found ourselves in an unpleasant situation with the taxi driver. For those who want to take a taxi, I recommend that you insist that the meter be used even if booked through the hotel. 
